{"word":"ἐπιδευής","slug":"ἐπιδευής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπιδευής</b></el> <el>(ἐπιδευής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> and ionic for <a href='S:ἐπιδεής'><el>ἐπιδεής</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>in need</i> or <i>want of</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>in want</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>lacking, failing in</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>βίης ἐπιδευέες Ὀδυσῆος</el> <i>inferior to</i> U. in strength, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>ἐπιδευέες ἦμεν</el> <i>too weak</i> were we, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}